# Platform UI Standards

Standards for the home page, welcome screen, level map, and shared UI elements. Every rule below comes from UNHCR branding requirements and feedback on the platform (Обратна връзка 2).

## Terminology

- **Platform title:** „Български език за **бежанци** A1" — NOT „мигранти". This applies to `<title>`, OG tags, `metadata`, README.
- **Level labels:** Always use **Latin letters** — A1, A2, B1, B2 (not А1, А2 with Cyrillic).

## UNHCR Branding

- **Primary color:** `#0072BC` (UNHCR blue). Use as primary action button color, link color, accent.
- **Logo:** UNHCR logo should be visible and reasonably large (not tiny).
- **Home button:** The UNHCR logo should act as a home button (link to `/`).
- **Reference:** https://dataviz.unhcr.org/download/UNHCR_Data_Visualization_Guidelines.pdf (page 4 for color palette).

## Welcome / Home Screen (after login)

After the user logs in and arrives at the level selection screen:

- Show: „Добре дошли, [Name]!" + „Изберете ниво:" + level cards (A1, A2, B1, B2).
- Do NOT show: „Изберете ниво, за да продължите обучението си." (redundant subtitle).
- Below the level cards: **Legend** (виж §Legend section).

## Welcome Screen (before login)

Text for the unauthenticated home page:

```
Добре дошли!
Това е платформа за изучаване на български език.
Тук ще намерите безплатни интерактивни уроци, упражнения и тестове за нивата А1, А2, B1 и B2.
Желаем ви успех!
```

## Legend (Platform Guide)

Location: bottom of the level-selection screen (after login), in [src/app/level/a1/LevelMapClient.tsx](mdc:src/app/level/a1/LevelMapClient.tsx) or a shared component.

The legend explains the platform's interactive elements. It must be translated on all 7 languages via `ui.ts`. Contents:

| Element | What to explain |
|---|---|
| 🔊 icon | Clicking it reads the word/phrase aloud |
| Green „Слушай" button | Plays the full audio for a text or dialogue |
| Dictionary icon | Opens the built-in dictionary for the current word |
| Chatbot button | Opens the AI language assistant (external link) |
| Grammar menu | Access to the grammar reference |
| Culture menu | Access to culture & lifestyle notes |
| Reset button | Resets all answers in the current exercise |

Screenshot images in the legend stay universal (no translation needed); only the text labels are translated.

## Audio UX Standard

- **Toggle on 2nd click:** Clicking the same audio element while it is playing should **pause** the audio, not restart. Clicking a different element stops current audio and starts the new one.
- **„Слушай" / „Спри"** button label switches during playback.
- This behavior must be consistent across: `Dialogues`, `ReadingText`, `IllustratedCards`, `GrammarTable`, `GrammarWithExamples`.

## Reset Button Standard

Every interactive exercise must have a **Reset** button that clears all user answers and resets the exercise to its initial state. The button appears in the same action bar as the „Провери отговорите" button. Missing Reset = UI bug.

## Info Box (Grammar Highlight)

For grammar notes that need visual prominence (not just a subtitle), use the `GrammarHighlight` component. It renders as a **green rounded box with ℹ icon**. Translated via `textKey` in `ui.ts`.

Example usage: the с/със rule (урок 2 упр. 12), the million/milliard rule (урок 5 упр. 31).
